obo:ECO_0005589  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_5526  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Lats1 is colocalized with PSD-95 at DIV18 (Fig. 7A) and, upon overexpression, Flag-tagged Lats1 co-localizes with GFP-actin in spines (Fig. 7F).. Experimental description: \"Dissociated cultures of primary hippocampal neurons were prepared from E18 Sprague-Dawley rat embryos...\" (p. 726)\nCommercial antibody Lats1 (1:2,000; NBP1-86860; Novus Biologicals).\n\"At 18 DIV, endogenous Lats1 was enriched in spines and overlapped with PSD-95 punctate (Fig. 7 A). No antibody cross-reactivity with exogenously expressed Lats2 was detected (Fig. S3A)...\" (p. 721).\nReviewed UniProt-Accs are only available for Human (O95835) and Mouse (Q8BYR2)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2023-11-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_5526" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

